This library contains many methods implemented from different publications, and not all publication are mine. 
Depending on the method from "src/" that you use, you will need to cite a different paper.

For Bryan method
DOI: 10.1007/BF02427376
DOI: 10.1016/S0146-6410(01)00150-8

For dual Newton method
DOI: 10.1088/1751-8121/adf924
DOI: 10.48550/arXiv.2604.27154

For the regularized stochastic optimization method (RSOM)
DOI: 10.48550/arXiv.2606.19205

for the stochastic analytic continuation with parallel tempering (SACPT)
DOI: 10.48550/arXiv.cond-mat/0403055

For the Backus-Gilbert method
DOI: 10.5555/1403886

For the Gaussian Backus-gilbert Method
DOI: 10.1103/PhysRevD.99.094508

To run this code, 
1) download it
2a) ./setup_venv.sh
(if you are on a cluster)
2b) srun --time 20:00:00 --pty bash -l -i
3) ./run_all_inversions.sh

If you need things to go fast, comment out the RSOM calls.
If you need things to go REALLY fast, then also comment out the dual Newton calls.
